{"schema_version":"1.7.5","id":"PYSEC-2018-155","published":"2018-11-12T02:29:00.233Z","modified":"2026-05-20T09:19:00.018398Z","aliases":["CVE-2018-18920","GHSA-vqgp-4jgj-5j64","PYSEC-2018-96"],"details":"Py-EVM v0.2.0-alpha.33 allows attackers to make a vm.execute_bytecode call that triggers computation._stack.values with '\"stack\": [100, 100, 0]' where b'\\x' was expected, resulting in an execution failure because of an invalid opcode. This is reportedly related to \"smart contracts can be executed indefinitely without gas being paid.\"","affected":[{"package":{"name":"evm-py","ecosystem":"PyPI","purl":"pkg:pypi/evm-py"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{}]}],"versions":["0.10.1b1"],"database_specific":{"source":"https://github.com/pypa/advisory-database/blob/main/vulns/evm-py/PYSEC-2018-155.yaml"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://twitter.com/AlexanderFisher/status/1060923428641878019"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://twitter.com/NettaLab/status/1060889400102383617"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/ethereum/comments/9vkk2g/netta_labs_claim_to_have_found_a_vulnerability_in/e9d3wyx/"},{"type":"EVIDENCE","url":"https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/1448"}],"severity":[{"type":"CVSS_V3","score":"CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H"}]}